HEADWORD: Tenace
<hw>Ten"ace</hw> <pr>(t⟦ecr⟧n"⟦asl⟧s)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[F.
<ets>tenace</ets> tenacious, demeurer <ets>tenace</ets> to hold the best
and third best cards and take both tricks, the adversary having to lead.
See <er>Tenacious</er>.]</ety> <fld>(Whist)</fld> <def>The holding by
the fourth hand of the best and third best cards of a suit led; also,
sometimes, the combination of best with third best card of a suit in any
hand.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Tenacious</ent>⟦br⟧
